<Base title="Simmer — Privacy Policy" doc>
  <nav><a href="/simmer/">← Simmer</a></nav>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="date">Effective July 3, 2026</p>

  <h2>The short version</h2>
  <p>Simmer collects nothing. Your timers are yours, and they never leave your device.</p>

  <h2>Your data</h2>
  <p>Timer names, durations, and presets are stored locally on your device. Your data never
     touches our servers, because we don't have any.</p>

  <h2>What we don't do</h2>
  <p>No accounts. No analytics. No ads. No third-party SDKs. No tracking of any kind.</p>

  <h2>Purchases</h2>
  <p>The one-time unlock is processed entirely by Apple through the App Store. We never see your
     payment details.</p>

  <h2>Changes</h2>
  <p>If this policy ever changes, the update will be posted on this page with a new effective date.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions? Visit <a href="/simmer/support/">Support</a>.</p>
</Base>
